node.text: One year ago today was your last day being alive. For months to follow, I had no vision of what my future would look like without you in it. The only thing I knew was that I had to carry on and try my best for our girls. Looking at these photos from around that time, I remember how lost I felt. I really didn’t think I had it in me. You were at the center of my life for 5 years. Who was I if not yours? Now a year later I feel like I have finally figured it out. For the first time ever, I love who I am. I’m growing, everyday, into the best version of myself. I wish more than anything that you could know this version of me. Maybe you always saw the best in me and I just couldn’t see it in myself. I’m so proud of how far I’ve come and I know you would be too. We miss you so much. 💙
